                                                                                                               SPORT BRIEFS
                                              Govt forms panel to   run RCA
    Jaipur: The Rajasthan government has formed an ad hoc committee to look after the work of the Rajasthan Cricket Association (RCA) executive committee, even as infighting between the two factions of the state governing body continues to take its toll on cricket.
    In his order, dated October 20, the registrar of co-operative societies, Rajasthan, Mukesh Sharma has appointed a nine-member committee with former Ranji playerRatan Singh as convener.
    Meanwhile, in another blow to the state cricket team, the CK Nayudu under-22 match between hosts Mumbai and Rajasthan, that was to commence in Mumbai Wednesday, was cancelled following the arrival of two teams claiming to represent the visitors.
    BCCI denial
    Mumbai: The Board of Control for Cricket in India has denied that the lone warm-up match of the forthcoming Sri Lanka series was ever scheduled to be played at the Motera Stadium in Ahmedabad.
    ldquo;The match (Australia vs Board President rsquo;s XI) was never to be played there, rdquo; BCCI Chief Administrative Officer Ratnakar Shetty said. His clarification came after an agency report said that host Gujarat Cricket Association had requested the Board to move the three-day game.
    Gayle game
    Discovery Bay: Chris Gayle will be happy to take on the West Indies captain rsquo;s role again, he has said. ldquo;If I am asked to do the job, I will be committed. It is always an honour to captain the West Indies, rdquo; Gayle said.
    Title sponsor
    Calcutta: The BCCI Wednesday announced that Hero Honda is the title sponsor of the ODI series against Australia and that the winning team will receive the Hero Honda Cup. 
    Lifters dazzle
    New Delhi: Sukhen Dey bagged gold in the junior men rsquo;s 56kg category as Indian weightlifters began their Commonwealth Senior and Junior Championship campaign in Penang with six gold and four silver Wednesday.
    Probe starts
    Budapest: Fifa has opened an investigation into Diego Maradona rsquo;s profanity-filled tirade on live television following a World Cup qualifying win.
    
